===Etymology===
Sanskrit ''avatara'': "descent (of a [[diety]] from [[heaven]] in [[incarnate]] form)", from ''ava-'' "down" and ''tariti'' "(he) crosses".

===Noun===
'''avatar'''
# ([[Hinduism]]) The earthly [[incarnation]] of a deity, particularly [[Vishnu]].
# (computing) A [[computer]] [[representation]] of a [[person]], for instance, in a [[role]] [[playing]] [[game]].

